1
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:14,920
My name is Lin Yuhan.

2
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:15,920
How are you?

3
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:17,360
I am fine.

4
00:01:17,360 --> 00:01:19,039
I am fine, thank you.

5
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:22,400
And you?

6
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:24,020
Let's read it again, okay?

7
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:27,360
How are you?

8
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:29,400
I am fine.

9
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,120
Thank you.

10
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:33,680
And you?

11
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:36,280
How are you?

12
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:37,840
Excuse me, can I join in?

13
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:40,400
Of course, the more the merrier.

14
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,000
Great.

15
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:45,200
Hello.

16
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:46,759
I am Yiyi.

17
00:01:46,759 --> 00:01:48,080
I am from Hubei.

18
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:51,320
Why not think of this as a place full of dreams?

19
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:53,200
My English is not bad, right?

20
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:57,320
Do you like ice cream?

21
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:58,560
Oh my god.

22
00:01:58,560 --> 00:01:59,960
Hey kids,

23
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:01,560
let's play a game.

24
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:04,880
Guess my favorite flavor.

25
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:06,840
I'll teach you a magic trick.

26
00:02:08,759 --> 00:02:09,320
Okay?

27
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:10,160
Okay.

28
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:14,720
Oh dear,

29
00:02:15,720 --> 00:02:17,520
if they're learning a foreign language, they should just learn.

30
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:19,920
Why are they jumping around outside?

31
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:23,040
What if they get hurt?

32
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:24,800
They are just kids.

33
00:02:25,079 --> 00:02:27,079
It's good for them to run and jump around.

34
00:02:27,079 --> 00:02:28,600
Consider it exercise.

35
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:33,320
His mom just won't listen to me.

36
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:36,320
It's much better to pay someone to teach at home.

37
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:38,579
It saves worry, effort, and it's not hot.

38
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:42,560
In this weather, what if he gets heatstroke?

39
00:02:44,079 --> 00:02:46,160
Kids nowadays,

40
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:49,560
it's great to have a companion to play with.

41
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:53,360
But they can't just play all the time.

42
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:56,360
If they keep playing, aren't they wasting time?

43
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:03,760
But this is their most carefree childhood.

44
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:09,040
Our baby can't lose at the starting line.

45
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,960
Everyone is on the same starting line.

46
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:12,880
The key is,

47
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:18,079
how many people can persist to the finish line?

48
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:22,960
My baby is going to study abroad when he grows up.

49
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:26,680
I heard they already use robots there.

50
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:30,360
It's so good in our country now,

51
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,960
why do they have to go abroad?

52
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,960
It's so good abroad.

53
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:36,280
Many people want to go abroad.

54
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:41,600
In the past, China was opening its eyes to see the world,

55
00:03:42,079 --> 00:03:43,320
but nowadays,

56
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:47,400
China is the focus of the whole world.

57
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,700
It's just that,

58
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:59,480
can they carry on

59
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:02,440
what our ancestors left behind?

60
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:08,920
School is over, let's go take a look.

61
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:09,840
Okay, let's go.

62
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,000
I didn't expect

63
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,160
Yiyi's English to be so good.

64
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:19,690
She really likes kids, too.

65
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:21,800
She learned English by listening to songs.

66
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,760
Despite her quirky behavior,

67
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:26,290
being a teacher has always been her dream.

68
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:29,440
Yaoyao,

69
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:30,240
water, quick.

70
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,480
I'm exhausted.

71
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:32,880
Please sit, Ms. Yiyi.

72
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,400
You sit here.

73
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:39,000
I didn't know our Director Zhang's English is so nice.

74
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,280
Yes, you speak it well.

75
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:43,560
You can speak English?

76
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:46,600
English is not difficult for me.

77
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:50,640
On the contrary, I feel I still need to learn more Chinese.

78
00:04:51,159 --> 00:04:51,960
Confidence.

79
00:04:52,159 --> 00:04:56,240
It's a sense of security and confidence formed by age and culture.

80
00:04:57,400 --> 00:05:00,000
So we can communicate in Mandarin.

81
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:00,920
Wow.

82
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:02,040
Old antique.

83
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:04,240
I couldn't tell your English is so good.

84
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,680
That's because you don't know

85
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,880
how hard it was for us to learn Mandarin.

86
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,860
You had to learn Mandarin too?

87
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:10,520
Of course we did.

88
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:11,120
Of course.

89
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,360
All overseas Chinese!

90
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,560
You are all overseas Chinese?

91
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:30,840
Where is your ancestral home?

92
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:31,800
I'm from Hujian.

93
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,120
Fujian,

94
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:33,920
not Hujian.

95
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:35,930
Where in Fujian?

96
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,530
Aimen Jimo (Xiamen Jimei).

97
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:39,840
Jimo?

98
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:40,720
Jimei Lang.

99
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,400
How about you?

100
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,690
I'm from Guangdong.

101
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:47,920
Forget it.

102
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:50,560
I'll teach you once now,

103
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:52,720
and then everyone read after me.

104
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:54,800
Persistence is victory.

105
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:57,040
Persistence is victory.

106
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,440
Persistence is victory.

107
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:03,680
Persistence is victory.

108
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:05,720
Teacher,

109
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:07,400
since we're all overseas Chinese,

110
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,520
why don't you come up with a slogan for us?

111
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:10,250
How about it?

112
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:15,440
How about,

113
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:16,440
All overseas Chinese,

114
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:17,400
what you have, I have too.

115
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:18,200
How is that?

116
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:18,840
Great.

117
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:19,640
This is good.

118
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:20,440
Great.

119
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:28,120
After all this time,

120
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:30,400
you started calling it Da Hujian so early,

121
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,920
or Jimei Lang.

122
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:34,120
I didn't expect you to have this skill.

123
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,960
From now on, I'll be your Chinese teacher,

124
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:37,320
and you'll be my English teacher.

125
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:39,080
You be my Chinese teacher?

126
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:43,200
Cultural confidence is our oxygen.

127
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:43,920
No need to shout,

128
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,640
confidence is in our every move.

129
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:48,120
The brush, ink, paper, and inkstone are weapons, not antiques.

130
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,120
Wang Xizhi's elegance,

131
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,159
Yan Zhenqing's character,

132
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:51,800
all continue in our genes.

133
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,840
What was that just now?

134
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:56,720
Chinese rap.

135
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:59,850
How could I be your Chinese teacher without some skills?

136
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:02,000
I couldn't tell, Yiyi.

137
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:04,330
You still know how to do this after so long?

138
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:06,400
You hid it well.

139
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:09,840
This time I'm quite curious,

140
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:11,720
to see how she transforms you.

141
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:13,920
Look how scared you are.

142
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:16,040
Just follow Ms. Zhang today.

143
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:30,920
Old antique, pick whatever you like.

144
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:32,050
It's my treat today.

145
00:07:35,159 --> 00:07:36,020
This is not bad.

146
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:39,520
This piece is nice.

147
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,580
I'll match it with some pants for you.

148
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:44,280
Look at the outfit I put together,

149
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:45,880
it's not bad either.

150
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:16,560
I think this outfit suits me better.

151
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:21,920
Lin Yaozu.

152
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:25,400
If you can't go back to the past,

153
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:27,210
will you be unaccustomed to it?

154
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:30,400
You have to slowly get used to current culture.

155
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:32,840
No.

156
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:34,730
I have things I like too.

157
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,720
Yiyi can teach me to sing.

158
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:39,960
What, are you addicted?

159
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:41,840
I charge for that.

160
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:42,520
Don't forget.

161
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:44,240
You haven't paid for your room yet.

162
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:46,240
Then please enlighten me, Mr. Zhang.

163
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,480
I'll study hard

164
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:48,480
to pay off my room.

165
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:50,760
You're a promising student.

166
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:16,120
Lin Yaozu.

167
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,480
Yiyi.

168
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:26,480
Yiyi, wake up. He's gone.

169
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,640
Who is gone?

170
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:29,160
Lin Yaozu.

171
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:30,680
Lin Yaozu is gone.

172
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:34,360
So what if he's gone?

173
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:36,960
Maybe he time-traveled back.

174
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,280
Isn't that great?

175
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:40,640
I can sleep a little longer.

176
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,480
Yiyi!

177
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:45,840
What?

178
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:47,080
He's gone?

179
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:49,040
He hasn't paid for his room yet.
